title: [ğŸ•‹ Subvert Your Perception] A mechanical watch hides a smart core! PEJE ZW06 New Product Review
ESR Classic Hybrid iPhone 17 Case Review â€“ Amazonâ€™s Top-Rated Case Failed My Drop Tests
description:
This is one of the most popular iPhone 17 cases on Amazon...thousands of five-star reviews, â€œmilitary-gradeâ€ protection claims, and all that influencer hype. But after running it through my full 30-drop test protocol, I honestly donâ€™t get the love. You get what you pay for.

Get your own ESR for iPhone 17 Pro Max Case, Camera Control, Compatible with MagSafe, Shockproof Military-Grade Protection, Magnetic Phone Case for iPhone 17 Pro Max, Classic Hybrid Case by using this link: https://mreh.ca/4qn15SV
*This is an Amazon affiliate link that will bring you to the right Amazon store for your location

#ReviewerNotInfluencer #Reviews #iPhone

In this video:
0:00 Intro
0:29 Design
0:47 Handling & Usability
1:45 Protection Features
2:55 Drop Protection
3:59 Should You Get It?

ESR for iPhone 17 Pro Max Case, Camera Control, Compatible with MagSafe, Shockproof Military-Grade Protection, Magnetic Phone Case for iPhone 17 Pro Max, Classic Hybrid Case Review

-Simple clear case
-Has oversized corners
-offers better clearance for the screen as well as the back
-handles like a typical clear case
-sliglyt tacky
-super smooth back
-nothing for your fingers to dig into
-fingerprints are going to be an issue
-weighs 38g
-quite a bit lighter than the previous case I reviewed, the Mous Limitless
-going to make your iPhone feel about 50% bigger
-for corner drops
-this thing was pretty good
-the iPhone recorded 9.4G's during impact, the Mous was 9.3G's
-overall, it was about 9% better than the average case

-however, with it's air bags and massive TPU corners, this case took much longer to settle
-32% slower than the average case

-surprisingly, the case didn't tend to tumble as rotation rate was slower than average (-18%)

-the total force on the iPhone for corner drops was 1.4Ns which is a hair below average which is good (-6%)

-now remember the weak ass top?
-well, this case fails my face first drop protection
-on a small face first drop, the case edge, despite having oversized corners, rolls off the iPhone
-which means iPhone screen, table, bad
-the next case I'm reviewing is the ESR Classic hybrid with a stand so the top of the iPhone is super rigid 

-how about the camera lump drops
-first of all, the camera lump on the case is all TPU
-which means the initial impact is slightly better than average
-the case settles at an average rate after the drop
-but the overall force going to the iPhone is  10% higher than average
-Now despite being really cheap
-ESR built some decent durability features
-things like the oversized corners and PC back help with protection
-corners are quite thick, sitting at 3.1mm ish, which is thicker the Mous limitless
-the corners also have air pockets

-one of the things I'm hoping to figure out in all my testing is to see if cases that use TPE like the Limitless actually perform better than cases that use basically air bags like this cheap ESR product

-the case does have a PC back but it only covers the glass portion of the back
-the camera lump area is just plastic
-the PC back does almost nothing for overall ridged as it took 11.9N to bend it 8mm
-that's 60% worse than the average iPhone case
-this is going to be an issue for this case in a few minutes
-First case in my 50 case review where the magnets are actually good
-12.2 Pull, 15.9 Push
-Better than the average iPhone case by 38%
-Don't have to worry about having a magsafe accessory fail
-Buttons are terrible
-Camera control is an actual button which is great
-expecting a plastic cover from budget brands
-will note that the port cutout has a nice chamfer to it so it's pinky friendly

title: Product Launch Funnel - Attention, Anticipation, and Action
description:
Most product launches fail because they rush straight to the offer.

The secret is to build anticipation before you ever start selling.

The Product Launch Funnel does exactly that. 

It turns curiosity into excitement and excitement into buyers, all through a simple four-part sequence.

Hereâ€™s how it works:

1. The Launch Page: Invite people to opt in and watch a short video that reveals the big idea.

2. Video 1: Show the problem and the promise of your solution.

3. Video 2: Teach something valuable and help them get a small win before they buy.

4. Video 3: Share stories and proof that your product works.

5. The Offer: On day four, open the doors with your full launch.

Each video builds trust, momentum, and connection so when itâ€™s time to sell, your audience is already ready to buy.

This funnel doesnâ€™t chase buyers. It creates them.

Comment â€œlaunchâ€ below and Iâ€™ll send you the whiteboard.

title: How To Prepare For a Product Launch | Drug Launch Excellence
description:
Tom Caravela sits down with Ramin Farhood to discuss the intricacies of product launches within the pharmaceutical industry. They explore indicators of a successful launch and lessons learned from past challenges. The conversation delves into market access, reimbursement, and the critical impact of team alignment. Ramin highlights the balance between speed and safety, the importance of compliance, and the dangers of siloed operations. They also consider the role of digital and AI, patient insights, and provide practical advice for companies preparing for their first launch

Mastering the Art of How to Prepare for a Product Launch
Ever wondered why some product launches are more successful than others? What if I told you that mastering the art of How to prepare for a product launch could be your key to success? In this video, we dive deep into the strategies that ensure a seamless and impactful launch.

Have you ever noticed how some companies achieve Drug Launch Excellence while others struggle? Understanding the role of a medical science liaison and the importance of medical affairs can make all the difference. Join us as we explore these critical components.

Understanding the Launch Process
The journey of How to prepare for a product launch begins with thorough planning. From market research to strategy development, each step is crucial. Our insights will guide you through the process, ensuring you achieve Drug Launch Excellence.

The Role of a Medical Science Liaison
A medical science liaison plays a pivotal role in bridging the gap between the company and healthcare professionals. Their expertise in medical affairs is invaluable for a successful launch. Discover how they contribute to achieving Drug Launch Excellence.

Career Advice for Aspiring Professionals
Looking for career advice in the pharmaceutical industry? Understanding How to prepare for a product launch can set you apart. Learn from experts who have achieved Drug Launch Excellence and gain insights into the world of medical affairs.

description:
DISPATCH EPISODES 3 & 4 First Look Trailer (AdHoc Studio)

Here is the first look trailer of Dispatch Episode 3 & Episode 4! 7 years since the old Telltale Games closed it's time we welcome AdHoc Studio a company mainly comprised of EX Telltale Staff with their first new title since their founding in 2018! Dispatch is finally here and it's finally time for a first look of Dispatch Episode 3 "Turnover" and Episode 4 "Restructure" This Dispatch Episode 3 & 4 Gameplay was captured on my PS5 PRO! Let's go for 1000 Likes! This Dispatch Walkthrough will contain the entire story with all cutscenes, a Review, all episodes, New Gameplay, New Characters, All Side Missions, and the Ending of the Single Player campaign. Here is Dispatch PS5 Gameplay! Dispatch, is an adventure game starring Aaron Paul and Laura Bailey where you're a dispatcher that manages a dysfunctional team of misfit heroes and strategize who to send to emergencies around the city, all while balancing office politics, personal relationships, and your own quest to become a hero. Dispatch is a superhero workplace comedy where choices matter. Manage a dysfunctional team of misfit heroes and strategize who to send to emergencies around the city, all while balancing office politics, personal relationships, and your own quest to become a hero. From the writers & directors of Tales from the Borderlands and The Wolf Among Us, Dispatch is a superhero workplace comedy set in modern day Los Angeles. Featuring an all-star cast from every corner of entertainment. title: 2025 Foton Tunland 4x4 Ute FIRST LOOK â€“ the ultimate bargain?
description:
The 2025 Foton Tunland V7-C 4x4 Review (Aus) is under priced and oversized. Itâ€™s VERY appealing on paperâ€¦ but whatâ€™s it like in the real world?

Is this Chinese ute the ultimate bargain or too cheap to be true? At just $42,990 before on-roads, the reborn Foton Tunland undercuts even the cheapest Ford Ranger 4x4 dual cab while offering maximum real estate for your money. Itâ€™s big!

With a 2.0-litre turbo-diesel mild hybrid engine producing 120kW/450Nm, an eight-speed ZF auto, BorgWarner 4x4 system with rear diff lock, and a solid 1050kg payload capacity, the specs look impressive on paper.

But can this Chinese workhorse deliver where the forgettable original Tunland failed a decade ago? Yesâ€¦ and no.

Thereâ€™s several quirks and mis-steps here that remind you this isn't a Japanese or European ute.

There's also no ANCAP rating until 2026, and questions remain about long-term reliability and dealer network support.

So is the Foton Tunland V7-C a dual cab bargain or a risky budget punt? With pricing sharper than GWM Cannon, JAC T9, and KGM Musso, you're getting massive space and capability for the money â€“ but it comes with compromises.

Watch our full video to see if this Chinese challenger is worth the gamble or if you should stick with established players.

title: FIRST LOOK: Adobe's NEW AI is INSANE!
description:
I'm on the ground here at Adobe MAX 2025, and the AI announcements are even bigger than I expected! In this video, I'm giving you my first hands-on look at the completely revamped Adobe Firefly, which is now a full video and audio creation suite. You'll see me test out the game-changing Generate Soundtrack to create copyright-free music from scratch, and then dive into the new Generate Speech tool, powered by both Adobe's own Firefly Speech model and a partnership with the incredible ElevenLabs. But the biggest surprise is the new multi-model world of image generation. Watch as I use my own photo as a reference to create brand new images with Google's Gemini 2.5 (Nano Banana), see how Flux Kontext Max completely transforms the scene, and even generate a wild Studio Ghibli version using OpenAI's ChatGPT Image modelâ€”all from a single interface. This is my raw, first reaction to what feels like the future of AI-powered creativity.

0:00 Intro from Adobe MAX
0:12 The BIG News: New Partner AI Models (Google, OpenAI & More)
0:28 Testing AI Generate Soundtrack in Firefly
2:16 Testing AI Generate Speech (with ElevenLabs)
3:36 All The New AI Models Inside Firefly

title: How Important Is Silhouette At Paris Fashion Week? - Designer Brands Spotlight
description:
How Important Is Silhouette At Paris Fashion Week? Have you ever wondered how fashion designers use shapes and forms to communicate their ideas on the runway? In this video, we explore the significance of silhouette at Paris Fashion Week and its impact on the fashion industry. Weâ€™ll explain what silhouette means in the context of fashion design and how it influences the overall perception of a collection. Youâ€™ll learn how different shapes reflect societal changes and cultural values throughout history, from the elegant hourglass of the 1950s to the relaxed forms of the 1970s. Weâ€™ll also discuss how contemporary designers push creative boundaries by experimenting with unconventional structures and exaggerated volumes, challenging traditional notions of beauty and style. 

Major fashion houses like Chanel, Louis Vuitton, and Dior rely heavily on silhouette to maintain their unique identities while evolving with current trends. Weâ€™ll show how the shapes presented on the runway often inspire seasonal styles seen in stores and on streets worldwide. Understanding silhouette is essential for appreciating how fashion communicates messages, reflects history, and drives innovation. Whether you're a fashion enthusiast or a professional, gaining insights into silhouette helps you better understand the art and evolution of fashion design. Weâ€™ll start by discussing the types of health data these devices can collect, including physical activity levels, vital signs like heart rate and oxygen saturation, and new sensors that detect biomarkers in sweat or other bodily fluids. 

Weâ€™ll explore how these innovations could enable doctors to receive real-time health updates, potentially catching signs of recurrence earlier than traditional methods. The video also highlights advanced technologies like AI-driven sensors that analyze tissue properties and microwave imaging techniques that create images of the lungs without invasive procedures. description:

In this video, we'll explore the different types of wearable devices that connect with the festival environment to make your time more seamless and immersive. We'll start by introducing RFID wristbands and how they simplify entry, payments, and tracking movements throughout the event. You'll learn how NFC-enabled badges provide quick access to VIP areas and facilitate exchanging digital information. Weâ€™ll also showcase LED wristbands that synchronize with music and stage effects, transforming the crowd into part of the show. Additionally, we'll discuss the role of smartwatches and smart glasses in helping festival-goers navigate large venues and stay updated with schedules. For a more sensory experience, weâ€™ll highlight Subpac wearable tech that transmits bass vibrations directly to your body, especially popular at electronic music festivals. title: Rivian Settles $250M Securities Class Action Lawsuit - Electric Vehicle News Update
description:
Rivian Automotive
Electric vehicles
Securities class action
$250 million settlement
2022 lawsuit
R2 vehicle launch
Rivian stock
Denies allegations
Insurance and cash payment
Accelerating zero-emission transportation
Rivian Automotive Inc settles securities litigation for $250 million without admitting fault. The company, known for innovative electric vehicles, can now focus on launching its mass market R2 model in 2026. Settlement covers claims from stock purchasers between November 2021 and March 2022. ABOUT LUDICROUS FEED

Ludicrous Feed is a Sydney-based YouTube channel showing daily life as an Australian family with an electric vehicle.

Tom and Joy provide straightforward candid insights into key issues around EV adoption such as vehicle range, charging infrastructure and road trip planning.

The channel started in 2018 after Tom purchased his Tesla Model S. The weekly live stream provides an opportunity for audience members to engage with others from the EV community as well as to stay up to date with the latest industry news. They have a Sigenergy home battery coupled with rooftop solar and together have reviewed many electric vehicles for the channel including brands such as BYD, Geely (Polestar, Volvo, Zeekr, Smart), Hyundai Motor Group (Kia, Genesis), SAIC (MG, LDV), GWM, Stellantis (Leapmotor, Peugeot, Fiat, Abarth, Jeep), VW Group (Cupra, Skoda), BMW Group (Rolls Royce, Mini), GM (Cadillac), Ford, Toyota, Subaru, Nissan, Renault, Xpeng, Chery and Deepal.

title: BYD EVs vs Local Council: Jamberoo Action Park's Fight to Store Electric Cars Off-Season
description:
BYD EVs storage controversy at Jamberoo Action Park. Discover how the world's top EV maker, BYD, is battling Kiama Council over off-season car parking.
In this video, we dive into the story of Jamberoo Action Park turning its massive car park into a temporary storage for thousands of new BYD electric vehicles during the off-season. As BYD overtakes Tesla as the global EV leader, strong demand in Australia has led to innovative solutions like this. But local complaints and zoning issues have sparked a development application rejection by the council.
Hear from park manager Matt George on utilizing the approved car park, the park's statement defending the low-impact use, Kiama Council's compliance actions, and BYD Australia's commitment to regulations. Explore the economic impacts on local businesses, the push for EV adoption in Australia, and why this 'car graveyard' label doesn't tell the full story.
Is this a sensible diversification for a seasonal theme park or a zoning violation? We break down the arguments, appeals process, and what it means for Australia's EV boom. Perfect for fans of electric vehicles, Australian news, and business battles.

ABOUT LUDICROUS FEED

Ludicrous Feed is a Sydney-based YouTube channel showing daily life as an Australian family with an electric vehicle.

Tom and Joy provide straightforward candid insights into key issues around EV adoption such as vehicle range, charging infrastructure and road trip planning.

The channel started in 2018 after Tom purchased his Tesla Model S. description:
This week on the Plugged-In Podcast, Patrick and Tim have lots of news: General Motors' big tech push at its GM Forward event, including Super Cruise where you don't have to watch the road, and Rivian's exciting new e-bike spinoff Also. Is Rivian about to deliver a reset on how e-mobility works? Tim tested one, and he loved it.

title: The ID. Buzz Gets BIGGER: $300\text{ Mile}$ Range, 3 Rows, and All the Retro Charm (2026 Model)
description:
The legend is reborn and scaled up! Get ready for an in-depth look at the 2026 Volkswagen ID. Buzz Long Wheelbase (LWB) model, the true spiritual successor to the iconic Microbus, now optimized for the American and global family markets.In this comprehensive review, we dive into every aspect of the ID. Buzz LWB, focusing on the changes for 2026 that make it the ultimate electric family hauler. The extended length finally allows for flexible seven-seater (2-3-2) and six-seater (2-2-2) configurations, with generous third-row legroom thanks to the long wheelbase and the clever MEB platform. We showcase the innovative Flexboard cargo system and the "Buzz Box" removable center console that make the cabin as versatile as it is charming.Under the hoodâ€”or rather, under the floorâ€”the 2026 ID. Buzz is expected to feature a larger $86\text{ kWh}$ battery option, boosting the estimated range to over $300\text{ miles}$ (approx. $480\text{ km}$). We also cover the exciting new ID. Buzz GTX variant, which delivers a powerful $335\text{ HP}$ dual-motor All-Wheel Drive (AWD) setup for those who demand performance with their retro-futuristic style.Inside, we explore the tech upgrades, including the rumored larger $12.9\text{ inch}$ infotainment system running the latest ID. software, the digital cockpit, and the available Panoramic Smart Glass Roof that switches from opaque to transparent. The interior is finished with sustainable, feel-good materials, staying true to the van's fun-loving ethos.From its retro two-tone paint schemes and distinctive LED lighting to its impressive fast-charging capability (up to $170\text{ kW}$ DC), the 2026 ID. Buzz is poised to be a game-changer, battling rivals like the Kia EV9 and Tesla Model Y. Watch to the end for our full verdict on price, practicality, and if this new electric icon delivers on the decades of hype.

title: Where Do Sustainable Designers Find Specialized Manufacturing Facilities?
description:
Where Do Sustainable Designers Find Specialized Manufacturing Facilities? Are you curious about how sustainable fashion brands find manufacturing facilities that align with their eco-friendly values? title: Kamal Gives His HONEST Shopping Review?so kamal dress review
description:
Kamal Gives His HONEST Shopping Review?Join me as I dive into a shopping spree and give my honest review on everything I buyâ€”let's see if it lives up to the hype!

I'm Kamal, and today I'm excited to share with you my recent shopping experience. I've been to several stores lately, and I thought it would be great to give you my honest review on what I bought, what I liked, and what I didn't.

One of the biggest challenges I faced was finding a store that had everything I needed. I was looking for a new pair of shoes, a few clothes, and some accessories, but it seemed like every store I went to was missing something. I spent hours hopping from one store to another, which was pretty frustrating. To make things worse, the customer service wasn't always the best. I encountered a few sales associates who seemed really disinterested in helping me.

The lack of product knowledge from the sales staff was another issue. I asked for recommendations on a few items, but they just pointed me in a general direction without giving me any specific suggestions. It felt like they were just trying to get rid of me. I also had trouble finding the right sizes for some of the clothes I wanted to buy.

When I finally found a store that had everything I needed, I was pleasantly surprised by the store environment. It was clean, well-organized, and had a great selection of products. I was able to find some amazing deals on some of the items on my list. The prices were a bit higher than I expected, but I felt like the quality was worth it. I also had a great interaction with one of the sales associates who was super helpful and knowledgeable about the products.

What really surprised me, though, was the follow-up email I received after my purchase. The store sent me a discount code and asked for my feedback on my shopping experience. It was a really nice touch and made me feel valued as a customer.

The most surprising insight from my shopping experience was how much of a difference good customer service can make. The store that provided excellent service ended up getting a lot more of my business, and I'm likely to return there in the future. On the other hand, the stores with poor customer service are probably going to lose my business. It's clear that investing in good customer service can pay off in the long run.

Another critical insight was the importance of having knowledgeable sales staff. When sales associates can provide valuable recommendations and help customers find what they're looking for, it makes a huge difference in the shopping experience.

The final insight was the value of follow-up communication. Getting a follow-up email that asked for my feedback and offered me a discount code made me feel like the store cared about my business.

All these experiences taught me that customer service, product knowledge, and follow-up communication are essential for a great shopping experience.

In conclusion, my shopping experience was a mixed bag, but it taught me some valuable lessons about what makes a great shopping experience. If you're a business owner, I hope you took away some useful tips from my review.

If you've had a similar experience, I'd love to hear about it in the comments. What are some of your favorite shopping experiences, and what do you think makes a great store? Let me know, and I might just feature your comment in my next video!

title: How Can Sustainable Designers Compete With Big Brands' Green Marketing? - Designer Brands Spotlight
description:
How Can Sustainable Designers Compete With Big Brands' Green Marketing? Are you curious about how independent designers can stand out in a market dominated by large brands? In this video, we'll explore the strategies that smaller, sustainable fashion brands use to build trust and connect with conscious consumers. We'll discuss the importance of transparency in sourcing materials, fair labor practices, and environmental impact. You'll learn how slow fashion principles and limited editions help reduce waste and promote longevity. We'll also highlight how craftsmanship and unique design set independent brands apart, creating products that are both meaningful and durable. Additionally, we'll cover innovative approaches like experimenting with new textiles, zero-waste techniques, and circular design models. Using social media and direct sales channels, these brands reach niche markets eager for authentic and responsible fashion choices. Building a compelling story around their values helps foster emotional bonds with customers and encourages loyalty. As sustainability becomes a key value for many consumers, emerging designers have the opportunity to redefine what it means to be a luxury brand by prioritizing genuine impact and transparency. Join us as we explore how small brands are making a big difference in the fashion industry through honesty, innovation, and commitment to responsible practices. Subscribe for more insights on designer brands, trends, and sustainable fashion.

title: What Strategies Do Sustainable Designers Use For Certified Materials? - Designer Brands Spotlight
description:
What Strategies Do Sustainable Designers Use For Certified Materials? Are you curious about how sustainable fashion brands choose their materials and ensure their products are environmentally responsible? In this video, we'll explore the key strategies that designers use to select certified, eco-friendly fabrics. We'll start by explaining the importance of third-party certifications like the Global Organic Textile Standard, Global Recycled Standard, OEKO-TEX Standard 100, and the Responsible Wool Standard. These certifications serve as trusted marks that verify the authenticity of sustainable materials, helping brands avoid misleading claims and giving consumers confidence in their choices. 

Next, we'll discuss how transparency in supply chains plays a vital role. Many brands now track materials from farm or factory to finished product, sometimes even providing digital passports to showcase the entire journey. We'll also cover how regenerative agriculture and the use of recycled fibers reduce environmental impact, while innovative bio-based fibers like pineapple leaf yarn are gaining popularity for their cruelty-free and eco-friendly qualities. 

Additionally, sustainable designers focus on waste reduction through efficient cutting techniques, zero-waste patterns, and eco-friendly dyeing processes. Many brands now produce detailed environmental impact reports, measuring their energy, water, and chemical use to ensure continuous improvement. 

If you're interested in understanding how fashion is shifting toward more responsible practices, this video provides a comprehensive overview of the strategies behind sustainable design. Join us to learn more about creating stylish, eco-conscious fashion that respects both people and the planet.

title: Abu Dhabi Global Food Week 2025: Meet the Exhibitors from Lebanon with Qoot
description:
Abu Dhabi Global Food Week 2025: Meet the Exhibitors from Lebanon with Qoot
.
QOOT, a Lebanese agri-food innovation cluster, organized the Lebanese Pavilion at the recent Abu Dhabi International Food Exhibition (ADIFE) 2025. The word "qoot" (Ù‚ÙˆØª) means "nourishment" in Arabic and represents the organization's mission to support innovation and sustainability in the agri-food sector. 
QOOT Cluster's role: As the Lebanese Agri-Food Innovation Cluster, QOOT organized the Lebanese participation at ADIFE 2025 to showcase Lebanese agri-food products and innovations.
ADIFE 2025: The exhibition is a major event for the food industry, and QOOT Cluster was proud to highlight the Lebanese pavilion.
Previous involvement: QOOT has also participated in past Abu Dhabi International Food Exhibitions, such as ADIFE 2022. 
.
.
ADIFE, a key event within Global Food Week, serves as a dynamic platform for the food and beverage industry. It unites global and regional leaders, offering buyers and suppliers unparalleled access to both local and international markets, fostering collaboration, innovation, and growth across the global F&B landscape.
.
Global Food Week is the regionâ€™s leading platform for dialogue, innovation, and partnerships around food security and agri-food systems. Whether you're a policymaker, industry expert, investor, or entrepreneur, connect with change-makers, discover transformative solutions, and shape a more resilient food future.

title: Astronaut's Guide to Space Food: Innovation, Taste, and Sustainability
description:
Space food innovation astronaut diet ISS food sustainable eating microgravity challenges ESA astronaut insights.
Discover how astronauts eat in space with insights from ESA's Rosemary Coogan. Explore unique challenges like altered tastes, growing fresh veggies on the ISS, and cell-based meat experiments. Learn about sustainable food tech for deep space missions and lessons for Earth.
Key topics include food preservation in microgravity, recycling water, and the emotional role of meals for astronauts' well-being. Uncover what foods astronauts miss most and how plant-based innovations could revolutionize space cuisine.
This video delves into NASA's Vegetable Production System, 3D bioprinted meat milestones, and the push for self-sustaining food in orbit. Perfect for science enthusiasts interested in space exploration and future food technologies.

title: FLIES AS HUMAN FOOD PART 1
description:
In this episode, I speak with Charity Kelsy, a researcher and mentor leading the way in insect farming, aquaponics, and regenerative agriculture. She explains how black soldier fly farming in Kenya is cutting feed costs for poultry and fish farmers, how cricket farming is creating new opportunities for edible insect businesses, and why young people and women are stepping into this fast-growing space.

From insect protein to waste recycling with BSF larvae, Charity shares practical advice for anyone interested in starting their own insect farm. We also dive into the basics of fish farming in Kenya, aquaponics systems, and the future of sustainable agriculture across Africa.

What youâ€™ll learn in this episode:

How to start insect farming in Kenya (step-by-step basics)

Why black soldier fly larvae (BSFL) are replacing expensive feeds like fishmeal and soy

The potential of cricket farming and edible insects for human nutrition

How insect farming supports circular farming systems & waste recycling

Opportunities for youth and women in insect farming businesses

The role of standards, regulations, and innovation in scaling insect farming

Whether youâ€™re a farmer, agripreneur, student, or just curious about the future of food in Africa, this conversation will give you fresh ideas and inspiration.

title: Bioprocessing surplus produce and industry by-products into premium ingredients and products
description:
Significant losses occur across the agri-food system, from surplus produce excluded due to size or appearance to nutrient-rich by-products generated during food processing. This seminar will showcase innovative bioprocessing strategies to valorise these underutilised resources. My work spans the solid-state fermentation of brewerâ€™s spent grain to enhance protein and prebiotic quality, and advanced identification and extraction of avocado bioactives from both processing residues and off-grade fruit. These approaches reduce waste, stabilise valuable nutrients, and deliver novel food and beverage applications. By bridging sustainability with innovation, we highlight opportunities for Queensland to lead in circular, value-added food systems.

Dr Jiahua Shi
Dr Jiahua Shi is a FaBA Senior Research Fellow at Centre for Nutrition and Food Sciences, QAAFI. With a strong foundation in fermentation, food science, analytical chemistry, and sustainable food systems, her research helps address critical industry challenges such as food waste reduction, upcycling of processing residues, development of novel food ingredients, and improvement of nutritional profiles in food and beverage products. She works closely with industry partners to deliver innovation and commercial impacts.

title: 5 Benefits of HEAVY Eccentric Overload!! Back Squat and Flywheel Combo
description:
Eccentric Training! My FREE ebook Movement Redefined Fundamentals explains all the training methods we use. Link at https://www.advancedhumanperformance.com/movement-redefined-fundamentals .

Best Shoes Vivobarefoot special sale 25% off code DRJOEL25. These shoes are scientifically shown to improve muscle function, strength, & joint health.
Clothing Greatness wins code JOEL25.
This is a continuation of yesterdayâ€™s post & topic.
Here Iâ€™m on the Kbox from Exxentric. This flywheel device provides intense eccentric loading via a unique form of iso-inertial training that creates strong levels of inertia the lifter must control throughout the set.
Eccentric overload has consistently shown in research to be one of the most effective strength training methods for enhancing physiological function & performance.
There are 5 benefits of eccentric overload which may occur at greater levels when compared to traditional weight training.
1.Increased motor unit recruitment.
2. Increased muscle growth.
3. Increased Strength & torque.
4. Increased Power & speed.
5. Improved joint health, tissue health, & injury prevention.
The 7 Eccentric Overload Methods (see yesterdayâ€™s post for more examples)
1. Partner assistance on concentric such as using greater than 1RM on bench press & partner assisting on way up.
2. Flywheel or Inertial training = gives greater eccentric force.
3.BANA 2:1 Bilateral Assisted Negative Accentuated (up with 2 down with 1 limb). You use roughly 70% 1RM for 2 limb variation.
4.Partner manual tension where partner gives added resistance on eccentric.
5. Biomechanical drop reps = adjust biomechanics mid rep so the concentric is a biomechanically more advantageous position than eccentric like Zottman curls.
6. Power Rack Eccentric Potentiation PREP = reduce load on concentric then add more weight on eccentric.
7. Specialized machines that add more eccentric tension like Vitruvian or Arena.

The kit includes a base station, a keypad, four contact sensors, one motion detector, two range extenders, a flood and freeze sensor, and a smoke and CO listener. This comprehensive package lays a solid foundation for a robust home security system, while also providing the potential for future expansion.

Installation of the Ring Alarm system is remarkably straightforward. The entire setup can be completed within a few hours, even for those who may not consider themselves particularly tech-savvy. The components come with clear instructions, and the user-friendly mobile app guides you through the process step-by-step. Each sensor is designed to be mounted easily â€“ whether on a door, window, or wall â€“ using adhesive strips or screws, which are included in the package. The only requirement is a reliable Wi-Fi connection, as the system operates wirelessly.

One of the standout features of the Ring Alarm system is its expandability. While the 14-piece kit covers most of the basic security needs for an average-sized home, users can easily add more devices as required. Ring offers a wide array of additional sensors, cameras, and smart home integrations, enabling users to customize their security setup to fit their unique needs. This flexibility is particularly advantageous for growing families or those who may move to larger homes in the future.

The base station acts as the heart of the system, providing a reliable connection between all devices and the Ring app. This app is well-designed and intuitive, allowing users to monitor their security system in real-time, receive alerts, and control various features from anywhere. The app also facilitates setting up customizable modes, such as "Home" and "Away," to cater to different security needs throughout the day. 

An important aspect of any security system is its reliability, and the Ring Alarm does not disappoint. The sensors are responsive, providing real-time notifications whenever a door or window is opened, or if motion is detected. The motion detector has a wide field of view, and the range extenders ensure that signals remain strong throughout larger residences. I found the accuracy to be commendable; false alarms were minimal, and the system successfully recognized standard movements within its designated range.

One feature that sets the Ring Alarm apart is its integration with other Ring products and smart home devices. For users who already own Ring cameras, doorbells, or smart lights, the app allows seamless connectivity, enabling the system to work harmoniously together. This integration means that, in the event of an alarm, users can automatically activate their security cameras or smart lights for enhanced monitoring.

The Ring Alarm system also offers professional monitoring services through their subscription plan. While the system can be used independently without a subscription, opting for professional monitoring adds an extra layer of security. The 24/7 monitoring ensures that, in the event of a security breach, emergency services can be quickly notified. Although this service incurs an additional monthly fee, many users find the peace of mind it provides to be worth the investment.

In terms of pricing, the Ring Alarm 14-Piece Kit is competitively positioned within the market. While there are cheaper options available, the comprehensive features, expandability, and quality of the components justify its price point. Moreover, the subscription for professional monitoring is also reasonably priced compared to other services, making it an attractive choice for budget-conscious consumers.

On the downside, some users may find that the app occasionally experiences connectivity issues, especially in areas with weak Wi-Fi signals. Additionally, while the system is designed for easy self-installation, those who prefer a more hands-on approach may wish for the option of professional installation, which is not available with this kit.

In conclusion, the Ring Alarm 14-Piece Kit stands out as a reliable, feature-rich, and expandable smart home security solution. Its ease of installation, real-time monitoring capabilities, and integration with other Ring products make it an excellent choice for anyone looking to bolster their home security.

The true magic of the Echo Dot lies in its integration with Alexa, Amazon's voice assistant. **Smart Home Capabilities**

The Echo Dot serves as an effective controller for a multitude of smart home devices. Its compatibility with a wide range of productsâ€”from smart bulbs and plugs to thermostats and security camerasâ€”allows for seamless integration into your smart ecosystem. Setting up devices is straightforward, and once connected, you can control them effortlessly through voice commands. 

Moreover, the Echo Dot supports Zigbee, allowing it to connect to a broader range of smart home devices without needing multiple hubs. This feature is particularly appealing for those who want to simplify their smart home setup. 

**Privacy and Security**

Amazon has made strides in addressing privacy concerns with the newest Echo Dot. Users can disable the microphone with a simple press of a button, ensuring that the device is not listening when you donâ€™t want it to. Additionally, Amazon provides transparency with its privacy settings, allowing users to review and delete voice recordings easily.

**Conclusion**

In summary, the latest Amazon Echo Dot is a powerful, versatile, and aesthetically pleasing smart speaker that offers excellent sound quality and seamless integration with Alexa.
